<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tinkering on yexca'Blog</title><link>https://blog.yexca.net/en/categories/tinkering/</link><description>Recent content in Tinkering on yexca'Blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><copyright>yexca</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 15:52:18 +0900</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.yexca.net/en/categories/tinkering/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Intranet Penetration with frp</title><link>https://blog.yexca.net/en/archives/281/</link><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 15:52:18 +0900</pubDate><guid>https://blog.yexca.net/en/archives/281/</guid><description>&lt;div class="notice ">&lt;strong>📢&lt;/strong> This article was translated by gemini-3.5-flash
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>Set up intranet penetration using frp with a full Docker deployment. Tested the speed, and it&amp;rsquo;s pretty good with acceptable latency.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="dns-configuration">DNS Configuration
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>You&amp;rsquo;ll need a server with a public IP. I handle my SSL certificates via Cloudflare, so all my connections go through port 80.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Configure a few domains pointing to your server: one for connecting to frp (e.g., &lt;code>frp.example.com&lt;/code>), and others for the services you want to proxy (e.g., &lt;code>server1.example.com&lt;/code>, &lt;code>server2.example.com&lt;/code>). Note that the frp connection domain (&lt;code>frp.example.com&lt;/code>) must not use Cloudflare proxying—keep it on &amp;ldquo;DNS only&amp;rdquo; mode.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Installing Xfce on CentOS 7</title><link>https://blog.yexca.net/en/archives/153/</link><pubDate>Sat, 17 Feb 2024 22:51:34 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.yexca.net/en/archives/153/</guid><description>&lt;div class="notice ">&lt;strong>📢&lt;/strong> This article was translated by gemini-3-flash-preview
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>&lt;del>When did I even write this? (&lt;/del>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="check-for-xfce-group">Check for Xfce Group
&lt;/h2>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">yum grouplist
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>If it&amp;rsquo;s not listed, you need to install the EPEL repository.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">yum install epel-release -y
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="install-x-window-system">Install X Window System
&lt;/h2>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">yum groupinstall &lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;X Window system&amp;#34;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="install-xfce">Install Xfce
&lt;/h2>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">yum groupinstall xfce
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="install-chinese-fonts-kaiti">Install Chinese Fonts (KaiTi)
&lt;/h2>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
